					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Brad on the class balance philosophy</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=324845" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/044581.html">To Brad and the Gang-Thought about Balance of Races, Class, etc.</a></B><P>

There should NOT be balance of power with everything. Some things are ment to whip the snot out of others, and some are ment to be weak than the rest. The weak always has their uniqueness and tricks, the powerful always has the great difficulty about it. Think about this, and try not to constantly CONSTANTLY Balance every little thing in the game. Everything is not balanced in anything nor should it ever be. Just thought I would express this opinion. <P>

<B>Actually, that opinion appears fairly similar to our core philosophy behind class balance, that people choose classes to play because that class appeals to them and because there are compelling reasons to play that class. And that, because EQ is a game with an emphasis on grouping, most classes play an important part when it comes to group interdependence.<P>

A literal balance of power (or how one class would stack up to another in combat, or against a particular mob) should always be secondary.<P>

-Brad</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=324845">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</table>



