	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   Is the question really about balance?  Or is it about being able to enjoy the game playing a class that you are or have grown attached to over time.  Personally I've spent over a year and a half building my ranger up to 48th level.  I do like to solo and just spend time playing the game without grouping.  Of course as most of us know thats near impossible with most classes...  especially Rangers(IMHO).  However, I do except that Verant wants EQ to be group based...  I respect that...  But how about enjoying the game.  Yeah I enjoy it when I get in a group...  But how about all those times I spend at a zone calling out for a group and no one wants me because I'm a Ranger that eats up the healers mana?  How many groups honestly say...  &quot;Ohh Ohh..  Quick get that Ranger!!!&quot;   Now how many actually jump for the Clerics and the Enchanters?  You see...  Grouping is great if you can get a group.  But when you spend two hours looking for a group...  running from zone to zone...   Gating from here to there.   It gets old and frustrating.  BALANCE IS AN ISSUE because it often effects how much we enjoy the game.  I don't want to be better than another class.  But I want a group to be equally excited about taking my class as a group member or I want to be able to go get some xp and loot solo.  One or the other without having to spend 2 or 3 hours just to get started.  I see people comment  &quot;If you don't like the class play something else...  Well I do like the class and I've built this one up and I don't want to throw it away!  Usually I have to run down friend I know in game to get a group out of sympathy for my situation.  On Rangers...  What do we offer a group?  Snare:  Oh yeah...  Definately my most used spell.  If Rangers didn't have snare we'd be almost useless in a group.  We dish out some serious damage...  Yeah...  If your able to get a hold of some real nice weapons(This means getting in groups to camp these nice weaps btw) which usually means taking on some serious damage as well.  Sow is nice..  Oh I forgot...  Druids can snare and sow as well... And Heal allot better...  DD, DOT, Damage Shields,  Evacs...  Tracking as it stands don't work to well...  I've tracked people in front of me to have them tell me they are behind me.  Try tracking a mob in Frontier Mountains and you'll see what I mean.  Archery?  46 damg Crit Hit once and Hour...  Nough said!  Oh yeah...  Get down deep in a dungeon and have to get out fast...  Casters Gate out..  Maybe even invis and make it out.  Warriors can hopefully takes some damage with there high AC and manage to crawl out.  Monks feign death, rouges may get lucky, evade hide and sneak and live to get out.  Oh well...  You've seen this all before so it's obviously NOT a Concern...<BR>
<BR>
Sincerly,<BR>
    A Frustrated Ranger having a bad day!  8)<BR>
<BR>
48th Ranger LFG<BR>
***Two Hours Later***<BR>
48th Ranger LFG  &lt;&lt;Please&gt;&gt;<BR>

