				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Personally, I like having rangers in the group so I can have somebody to goof on. They look like dorks with those hats.<BR>
<BR>
Seriously, as a shaman, grouping with rangers is useful, as they heal me while I cannidance. Plus, I put them on the same level as monks for maintenance - i.e., keeping them healed/buffed/speeded. I tend to make rangers &amp; monks more offensibly capable so that the fight will be over faster. I tend to make warriors, pallys and SKs tougher so that I can med while they take out the mob.<BR>
<BR>
Look at which race tends to play rangers - wood elfs. Their str &amp; sta are puling, and even though they have high agi, it doesn't add that much to AC. Wood elfs just aren't suited to being tanks, even though their offensive abilities are good. Maybe with all these new &quot;proc&quot; spells they're getting, rangers will become a force to be reckoned with. I was grouped with a ranger who was doing hand-to-hand with the mobs and prccing Wind Buffets. I'm not sure what he used to do that, but he sure was causing a lot of stuns!
				</font>
